'''''Nine Suitcases''''' is a one-man stage play adapted for theatre and performed by British actor David Prince from the [[Holocaust]] memoirs of [[Béla Zsolt]] as translated from Hungarian into English by Ladislaus Lob.<ref>Béla Zsolt, ''Nine Suitcases''; translated by Ladislaus Lob. London: Jonathan Cape, 2004 {{ISBN|0-224-06305-7}}; London: Pimlico Publishing, 2005</ref> Music was composed and performed by Bethan Morgan. It was directed by Lynn Hunter.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Klayman|first1=Deborah|title=ED FRINGE 2011: Nine Suitcases – Venue 13|url=http://www.thepublicreviews.com/ed-fringe-2011-nine-suitcases-%E2%80%93-venue-13/|website=ThePublicReviews.com|accessdate=13 September 2014}}</ref>

